(144, 1, '2016-06-29 22:19:58', '2016-06-29 16:19:58', '<h2 class="gdlr-heading-shortcode " style="text-align: center;"><span style="color: #003366;">School Curriculum</span></h2>\r\nAll subjects are taught in accordance with the National Curriculum. Bangla is the medium of instruction.\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">We teach here in two curriculum. Students of this institute will be learned at general education as well as Islamic Education like Quran, Hadith and many other Islamic knowledge. They will be able to serve the nation in many ways. So we are proud enough to say that, this institute is a home of Islamic &amp; General Education.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #ff0000;"><strong>General Section:</strong></span> This section is like the common section of any other school. According to our Acknowledgement, our government has stopped the PEC examination which has been continued From 2009 to 2015. So we are now trying to prepare our student to do better in JSC Examination in Class 8. Step by step it will increase to SSC level. But we have all the classes as a standard school.</p>\r\n\r\n<h5 style="text-align: center;"></h5>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h5 style="text-align: center;"></h5>\r\n<h5 style="text-align: center;">Subjects for JSC According NCTB</h5>\r\n<table class="style-2 table table-bordered aligncenter" style="height: 204px;" border="0" width="501" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>01. Bangla 1</td>\r\n<td>9. Physical Education</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>02. Bengla 2</td>\r\n<td>10. ICT</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>03. English 1</td>\r\n<td>11. Arts &amp; Crafts</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>04. English 2</td>\r\n<td>12. Work &amp; Life oriented Education</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>05. Mathematics</td>\r\n<td>13. Agricultural Studies (Additional)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>06. Science</td>\r\n<td></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>07. Banglaesh and Global Studies</td>\r\n<td></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>08. Islamic &amp; Moral Studies</td>\r\n<td></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #ff0000;"><strong>\r\nArabic Section:</strong></span> This institute is one of different institutes of Bangladesh which offers to learn Islamic knowledge along with the General Education. Student are taught here the Quran and they are able to memorize that fully. Apart this, we have ''Kitab'' division here in which students are taught the higher studies of Islam.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">We have a chance for students to attend at Exam Of Hifz Organized by <em>''Befaqul Madarisil Arabia Bangladesh''</em></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"></p>', 'CURRICULUM', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '60-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-06-29 22:19:58', '2016-06-29 16:19:58', '', 60, 'http://labibacademy.net/60-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(145, 1, '2016-06-29 22:53:13', '2016-06-29 16:53:13', '<h2 class="gdlr-heading-shortcode " style="text-align: center;"><span style="color: #003366;">School Curriculum</span></h2>\nAll subjects are taught in accordance with the National Curriculum. Bangla is the medium of instruction.\n<p style="text-align: justify;">We teach here in two curriculums. Students of this institute will be learned at general education as well as Islamic Education like Quran, Hadith and many other Islamic knowledge. They will be able to serve the nation in many ways. So we are proud enough to say that, this institute is a home of Islamic &amp; General Education.</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #ff0000;"><strong>General Section:</strong></span> This section is like the common section of any other schools. According to our acknowledgement, we have two national examination from class 1 to Class 8. One is at class 5 Which is known to all as PEC and the another one is at class 8 named as JSC. So we are now trying to give our best teaching and prepare our students to do better in Both Examination Gradually we will increase our study level to Class 12. But now we have the classes from nursery to class 8 now as a standard Junior Secondary School.</p>\n\n<h5 style="text-align: center;"></h5>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>Subjects For PEC According to NCTB</strong></p>\n\n<table style="height: 156px;" width="462">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td width="181">Bangla</td>\n<td width="186">Science</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width="181">English</td>\n<td width="186">Bangladesh &amp; Global Studies</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width="181">Mathematics</td>\n<td width="186">Islamic &amp; Moral Studies</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<div class="row"></div>\n<h5 style="text-align: center;"></h5>\n<h5 style="text-align: center;">Subjects for JSC According to NCTB</h5>\n<table class="style-2 table table-bordered aligncenter" style="height: 204px;" border="0" width="501" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>01. Bangla 1</td>\n<td>9. Physical Education</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>02. Bengla 2</td>\n<td>10. ICT</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>03. English 1</td>\n<td>11. Arts &amp; Crafts</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>04. English 2</td>\n<td>12. Work &amp; Life oriented Education</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>05. Mathematics</td>\n<td>13. Agricultural Studies (Additional)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>06. Science</td>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>07. Banglaesh and Global Studies</td>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>08. Islamic &amp; Moral Studies</td>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #ff0000;"><strong>\nArabic Section:</strong></span> This institute is one of different institutes of Bangladesh which offers to learn Islamic knowledge along with the General Education. Student are taught here the Quran and they are given a system to memorize the Quran Completely. Apart this, we have ''Kitab'' division here in which students are taught the higher studies of Islam.</p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;">We provide a chance for students to attend at Exam Of Hifz Organized by <em>''Befaqul Madarisil Arabia Bangladesh''</em></p>\n<p style="text-align: justify;"></p>', 'CURRICULUM', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '60-autosave-v1', '', '', '2016-06-29 22:53:13', '2016-06-29 16:53:13', '', 60, 'http://labibacademy.net/60-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(146, 1, '2016-06-29 22:41:37', '2016-06-29 16:41:37', '<h2 class="gdlr-heading-shortcode " style="text-align: center;"><span style="color: #003366;">School Curriculum</span></h2>\r\nAll subjects are taught in accordance with the National Curriculum. Bangla is the medium of instruction.\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">We teach here in two curriculums. Students of this institute will be learned at general education as well as Islamic Education like Quran, Hadith and many other Islamic knowledge. They will be able to serve the nation in many ways. So we are proud enough to say that, this institute is a home of Islamic &amp; General Education.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #ff0000;"><strong>General Section:</strong></span> This section is like the common section of any other schools. According to our Acknowledgement, we have two national examination from class 1 to Class 8. One is at class 5 Which is known to all as PEC and the another one is at class 8 named as JSC. So we are now trying to give our best teaching and prepare our students to do better in Both Examination Gradually we will increase our study level to Class 12. But now we have the classes from nursery to class 8 now as a standard Junior Secondary School.</p>\r\n\r\n<h5 style="text-align: center;"></h5>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h5 style="text-align: center;"></h5>\r\n<h5 style="text-align: center;">Subjects for JSC According to NCTB</h5>\r\n<table class="style-2 table table-bordered aligncenter" style="height: 204px;" border="0" width="501" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>01. Bangla 1</td>\r\n<td>9. Physical Education</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>02. Bengla 2</td>\r\n<td>10. ICT</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>03. English 1</td>\r\n<td>11. Arts &amp; Crafts</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>04. English 2</td>\r\n<td>12. Work &amp; Life oriented Education</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>05. Mathematics</td>\r\n<td>13. Agricultural Studies (Additional)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>06. Science</td>\r\n<td></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>07. Banglaesh and Global Studies</td>\r\n<td></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>08. Islamic &amp; Moral Studies</td>\r\n<td></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #ff0000;"><strong>\r\nArabic Section:</strong></span> This institute is one of different institutes of Bangladesh which offers to learn Islamic knowledge along with the General Education. Student are taught here the Quran and they are given a system to memorize the Quran Completely. Apart this, we have ''Kitab'' division here in which students are taught the higher studies of Islam.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">We provide a chance for students to attend at Exam Of Hifz Organized by <em>''Befaqul Madarisil Arabia Bangladesh''</em></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"></p>', 'CURRICULUM', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '60-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-06-29 22:41:37', '2016-06-29 16:41:37', '', 60, 'http://labibacademy.net/60-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
